songs.title: Stress Rap

description.plain:
The Rotten Apple is known to be a city with a rather dangerous environment. The same was true during the 90’s, but the crime rate was even bigger: two thousand two hundred and forty-five murders occurred in 1990.

Here both MC’s describe the struggle of living in Harlem, the neighborhood they grew in. It’s titled as Stress Rap as it describes the stress caused by the environment. In the end, Vast Aire points MCeeing as a way to break the cycle of violence.

Ironically or not, while the crime rate in New York dropped in the millenium, Harlem faces yet another social conflict – the problem of gentrification.

description.plain:
The 10th song on Cannibal Ox’s The Cold Vein is a posse cut featuring C-Rayz Wals (also a Def Jux fellow) and L.I.F.E. Long

Every verse is a description about how the battle unfolds, on the MCs preparing for an imaginary war and spitting battle rap verses.

The recurring motif is the protection of Asgard, which in Norse mythology is the home of the Æsir, the main pantheon of the Norse religion and the kingdom of the god Odin.

Conceptually, the song is an allusion to Ragnarök, an event in germanic mythology which is akin to the Apocalypse in the christian culture. In the events of the Ragnarök, where some of the most well known gods dies (such as Odin, Thor, Loki and Heimdallr, to name a few), Asgard ends destroyed.

“Carnivorous” is a battle rap containing line after line of animal imagery, puns, metaphors and allusions.

For the heads still pondering over the eLZhi verse, the creatures mentioned in order are:

Lions, tigers, alligators, rattlesnakes, seafood (see food), muscles, clams, slugs, snails, dogs, hogs, fleas, streak (microbiology), hawks, parakeets, owls, cockroaches, flies, bears, octopi, bed bugs, chicken, fish, cats, pigs, mice, rats and pigeons.
